<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,151,176]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Recognizable by the yellow posteromedian part of tergite 
<quantity box="[1014,1061,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
combination with the unsulcate scutellum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,223,248]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Notes.</emphasis>
The female from 
<collectingCountry box="[503,571,223,248]" name="Brazil" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Brazil</collectingCountry>
is darker in overall colouration: the scutellum has two blackish marks posteroventrally, tergites 
<number box="[445,459,260,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="3.0">3</number>
and 
<number box="[525,539,260,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="4.0">4</number>
are black with yellow posterior margins (tergite 
<number box="[1130,1144,260,284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="3.0">3</number>
also with yellow lateral margins).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
